This module has a go.mod and an internal/ tree but NO Go code: it models the pure
DESIGN phase of a Method project (committed design JSON, no implementation yet). The
methodcheck.Check design-only test points its arch.Spec at it so the load yields zero
classified packages — exercising the "skip arch layer rules + alignment when no code"
branch (arch.Check must NOT be called on a zero-package set). A real consuming repo at
the design phase has exactly this shape.
